<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="67" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="67">
This is new record to Zhejiang. The species is extremely similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium bayibini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="67" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bayibini">Scaphidium bayibini</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished by the slender antennal club, the elytra each with the inner black dot of basal fascia touching basal stria and the different shape of the aedeagal sclerites.
</paragraph>
